Police in Goodwood in Cape Town have arrested three men in connection with truck hijacking, Western Cape police said on Saturday. The men were arrested by members of the Goodwood crime prevention unit at about 2pm on Friday, Captain FC van Wyk said. The suspicious vehicle was spotted in Alice Street and pulled off the road. After the police stopped the truck the one suspect alleged that he was busy delivering liquor and was on his way to Langa. However, the hijacking victim in turn informed the police officers that the men had hijacked the truck and instructed him to drive to Langa. Three suspects aged 37, 27, and 26 respectively were arrested. They are from Khayelitsha, Nyanga, and Philippi. The truck was transporting liquor to the value of R700,000. No firearms were found on the suspects, Van Wyk said.